00:06:55.380 --> 00:06:57.330
My first question is a very basic one,

00:06:57.330 --> 00:07:00.130
which is, what is a psychedelic?

00:07:00.130 --> 00:07:01.500
We hear this term all the time,

00:07:01.500 --> 00:07:05.920
but what qualifies a
substance as a psychedelic?

00:07:05.920 --> 00:07:09.250
- Nomenclature is a real challenge

00:07:09.250 --> 00:07:10.760
in this area of psychedelics.

00:07:10.760 --> 00:07:12.943
So starting with the word psychedelic,

00:07:14.040 --> 00:07:18.080
if you're a pharmacologist,
it's not very satisfying,

00:07:18.080 --> 00:07:20.440
because that term really

00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:23.510
spans different pharmacological classes.

00:07:23.510 --> 00:07:24.343
In other words,

00:07:24.343 --> 00:07:26.280
if you're really concerned
about receptor effects

00:07:26.280 --> 00:07:29.120
and the basic effects of a compound,

00:07:29.120 --> 00:07:32.720
it spans several classes of compounds.

00:07:32.720 --> 00:07:34.100
But overall...

00:07:34.100 --> 00:07:37.140
So it's really more of a cultural term,

00:07:37.140 --> 00:07:42.140
or it does have a
relationship to drug effects,

00:07:42.720 --> 00:07:44.940
but it's at a very high level.

00:07:44.940 --> 00:07:47.070
So all of the so-called psychedelics

00:07:47.070 --> 00:07:51.160
across these distinct classes

00:07:51.160 --> 00:07:52.763
that I can talk more about,

00:07:54.190 --> 00:07:56.550
the way I put it, is
they all have the ability

00:07:56.550 --> 00:08:00.550
to profoundly alter
one's sense of reality,

00:08:00.550 --> 00:08:02.100
and that can mean many things.

00:08:02.100 --> 00:08:03.680
Part of that is profoundly altering

00:08:03.680 --> 00:08:06.070
the sense of self acutely,

00:08:06.070 --> 00:08:09.600
so when someone's on the psychedelic.

00:08:09.600 --> 00:08:13.210
So the different classes that can be,

00:08:13.210 --> 00:08:15.680
the specific pharmacological classes

00:08:15.680 --> 00:08:17.690
that can be called a psychedelic,

00:08:17.690 --> 00:08:21.200
are, one, what are called
the classic psychedelics.

00:08:21.200 --> 00:08:23.403
So in the literature,
you'll see that term.

00:08:24.520 --> 00:08:26.700
Hallucinogen and psychedelic all have

00:08:26.700 --> 00:08:29.750
traditionally been used synonymously.

00:08:29.750 --> 00:08:31.380
I think there was a
little of of a tendency

00:08:31.380 --> 00:08:32.213
to stay away from psychedelics,

00:08:32.213 --> 00:08:33.420
because of the baggage,

00:08:33.420 --> 00:08:36.870
but there's been a return to
that in the last several years.

00:08:36.870 --> 00:08:39.500
But the classic psychedelics
or classic hallucinogens

00:08:39.500 --> 00:08:44.210
are things like LSD, psilocybin,

00:08:44.210 --> 00:08:47.190
which is in so-called magic mushrooms.

00:08:47.190 --> 00:08:49.030
It's in over 200 species

00:08:49.030 --> 00:08:50.963
that we know of so far of mushrooms.

00:08:51.956 --> 00:08:53.830
Dimethyltryptamine, or DMT,

00:08:53.830 --> 00:08:57.473
which is in dozens and dozens of plants.

00:08:58.330 --> 00:09:00.807
Mescalin, which is in the peyote cacti,

00:09:00.807 --> 00:09:03.740
and some other cacti, like San Pedro.

00:09:03.740 --> 00:09:06.400
And even amongst these
classic psychedelics

00:09:07.640 --> 00:09:10.910
there are two structural,
structural classes.

00:09:10.910 --> 00:09:11.860
So that's the chemistry.

00:09:11.860 --> 00:09:14.000
There's the tryptamine-based compounds,

00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:16.220
like psilocybin and DMT,

00:09:16.220 --> 00:09:19.130
and then there's the
phenethylamine-based compounds.

00:09:19.130 --> 00:09:20.400
So these are the basic,

00:09:20.400 --> 00:09:23.350
two of the, basically, building blocks

00:09:23.350 --> 00:09:24.330
that you're starting from,

00:09:24.330 --> 00:09:28.020
either a tryptamine structure
or a phenethylamine structure.

00:09:28.020 --> 00:09:29.690
But that's just the chemistry.

00:09:29.690 --> 00:09:31.080
All of the...

00:09:31.080 --> 00:09:32.290
What's more important,

00:09:32.290 --> 00:09:34.660
or at least to someone like me,

00:09:34.660 --> 00:09:36.020
are the receptor effects,

00:09:36.020 --> 00:09:38.090
and then, ultimately, that's
going to have a relationship

00:09:38.090 --> 00:09:40.040
to the behavioral and subjective effects.

00:09:40.040 --> 00:09:42.310
So all of these classic psychedelics

00:09:42.310 --> 00:09:44.580
serve as agonist, or partial agonists,

00:09:44.580 --> 00:09:47.310
at the serotonin 2A receptor,

00:09:47.310 --> 00:09:49.890
so a subtype of serotonin receptor.

00:09:49.890 --> 00:09:52.480
Then you have these other classes of

00:09:54.110 --> 00:09:56.680
compounds that you could call psychedelic.

00:09:56.680 --> 00:09:59.270
Another big one would
be the NMDA antagonist.

00:09:59.270 --> 00:10:02.420
So this would include ketamine, PCP,

00:10:02.420 --> 00:10:03.500
and dextromethorphan,

00:10:03.500 --> 00:10:04.930
something I've done some research with,

00:10:04.930 --> 00:10:07.770
which folks might recognize
from like Robo-tripping,

00:10:07.770 --> 00:10:11.790
guzzling cough syrup,

00:10:11.790 --> 00:10:12.900
which is something kind of like

00:10:12.900 --> 00:10:14.343
high school kids are known to do

00:10:14.343 --> 00:10:16.070
when they can't get ahold of real drugs,

00:10:16.070 --> 00:10:17.400
that type of thing.

00:10:17.400 --> 00:10:22.400
So a large overlap in the
types of subjective effects

00:10:23.060 --> 00:10:24.610
that you get from those compounds

00:10:24.610 --> 00:10:29.120
compared to the 2A agonist
classic psychedelics.

00:10:29.120 --> 00:10:29.953
But then you have...

