00:37:36.470 --> 00:37:38.500
that does take place in your lab.

00:37:38.500 --> 00:37:42.363
So we're using a sort of generic
case example, if you will.

00:37:43.400 --> 00:37:44.490
The letting go of control

00:37:44.490 --> 00:37:46.110
is an interesting feature, actually,

00:37:46.110 --> 00:37:49.800
because one of the common
themes of good psychoanalysis,

00:37:49.800 --> 00:37:51.380
or psychotherapy of any kind,

00:37:51.380 --> 00:37:53.090
is that there's a trust built

00:37:53.090 --> 00:37:55.690
between the patient and the analyst,

00:37:55.690 --> 00:37:57.550
and that relationship becomes

00:37:57.550 --> 00:38:00.340
a template for trust more generally,

00:38:00.340 --> 00:38:01.810
and trust in one's self.

00:38:01.810 --> 00:38:04.740
It's actually, the end goal
of a good psychoanalysis

00:38:04.740 --> 00:38:06.240
is that the patient actually...

00:38:06.240 --> 00:38:07.120
One of the end goals

00:38:07.120 --> 00:38:09.410
is that they develop an
empathy for themselves,

00:38:09.410 --> 00:38:11.280
which almost sounds like an oxymoron,

00:38:11.280 --> 00:38:13.590
but if you spend a little
time with that statement,

00:38:13.590 --> 00:38:15.160
it actually pans out.

00:38:15.160 --> 00:38:20.160
So the psychedelic
experience is one in which,

00:38:20.460 --> 00:38:25.460
chemically, you're under a
new set of conditions, right?

00:38:25.670 --> 00:38:27.180
- Yeah.
- Let's coarsely,

00:38:27.180 --> 00:38:31.610
space and time are altered
in some way, sense of self.

00:38:31.610 --> 00:38:33.130
For instance, I might be going to

00:38:33.130 --> 00:38:35.220
a strongly interoceptive mode

00:38:35.220 --> 00:38:36.290
where I'm focusing on

00:38:36.290 --> 00:38:37.950
everything within the confines of my skin.

00:38:37.950 --> 00:38:40.360
Whereas, normally, we're
sort of interacting in space,

00:38:40.360 --> 00:38:41.940
and pens, and conversation.

00:38:41.940 --> 00:38:45.080
[mumbles] Occasionally, I'll
pay attention to my breathing,

00:38:45.080 --> 00:38:46.630
but I'm sort of dilating

00:38:46.630 --> 00:38:48.100
and contracting my focus for

00:38:48.100 --> 00:38:50.350
different things all the time.
- Yeah.

00:38:50.350 --> 00:38:52.860
- The letting go of control,

00:38:52.860 --> 00:38:54.900
it seems, to me, could be sort of

00:38:54.900 --> 00:38:57.560
the expansion of one perceptual bubble,

00:38:57.560 --> 00:39:01.300
to the point where you're
not actually worried

00:39:01.300 --> 00:39:03.650
that that perceptual bubble
is going to pop, or that,

00:39:03.650 --> 00:39:06.160
meaning you're not worried
about what people think of you.

00:39:06.160 --> 00:39:06.993
- [Dr. Matthew] Yeah.

00:39:06.993 --> 00:39:08.130
You're not worried whether

00:39:08.130 --> 00:39:10.560
or not your brain is going to explode,

00:39:10.560 --> 00:39:12.660
even though a thought could feel enormous.

00:39:13.780 --> 00:39:14.650
If I keep going like this,

00:39:14.650 --> 00:39:15.970
it almost sounds psychedelic,

00:39:15.970 --> 00:39:18.070
but that's the idea here.

00:39:18.070 --> 00:39:19.810
Or if I'm paying attention, for instance,

00:39:19.810 --> 00:39:21.720
to some Somatic experience,

00:39:21.720 --> 00:39:26.660
like the coursing of waves
of heat through my body,

00:39:26.660 --> 00:39:30.570
that I'm not suddenly
saying, "Is that weird?"

00:39:30.570 --> 00:39:32.830
I'm actually just going
deeper and deeper into it.

00:39:32.830 --> 00:39:35.763
So it's, essentially, expanding
a perceptual phenomenon.

