00:41:03.070 --> 00:41:04.680
Simply keep applying stimuli,

00:41:04.680 --> 00:41:06.140
and there's less response.

00:41:06.140 --> 00:41:07.410
This is what organisms do.

00:41:07.410 --> 00:41:08.650
This is what we have to do.

00:41:08.650 --> 00:41:10.120
And it's like there's this disc

00:41:10.120 --> 00:41:12.870
habituation component that-
- Disc habituation?

00:41:12.870 --> 00:41:13.703
- Yeah, so like we wouldn't
- Yeah.

00:41:13.703 --> 00:41:14.940
- be able to get through life,

00:41:14.940 --> 00:41:17.730
we wouldn't be able to cross
that street if we were like,

00:41:17.730 --> 00:41:19.963
whoa, this is a miracle.

00:41:19.963 --> 00:41:21.310
You know? [laughs]
- Well, I'm so glad you-

00:41:21.310 --> 00:41:22.730
No, I'm so glad you brought this up.

00:41:22.730 --> 00:41:25.210
I mean, here, I'm reflecting
my bias as a vision scientist,

00:41:25.210 --> 00:41:26.790
but most people don't realize this,

00:41:26.790 --> 00:41:28.240
but if you look at something long enough,

00:41:28.240 --> 00:41:29.850
it eventually disappears.

00:41:29.850 --> 00:41:31.540
It doesn't actually disappear,

00:41:31.540 --> 00:41:33.060
but perceptually, it disappears.

00:41:33.060 --> 00:41:34.450
You have these little microsaccades

00:41:34.450 --> 00:41:35.930
that ensure that it doesn't.

00:41:35.930 --> 00:41:36.970
- Right.
- But most of us

00:41:36.970 --> 00:41:39.470
don't look at any one thing for very long.

00:41:39.470 --> 00:41:40.303
- [Dr. Matthew] Right.

00:41:40.303 --> 00:41:41.800
- The brain's default is to

00:41:41.800 --> 00:41:44.670
perceptually jump around like crazy

00:41:44.670 --> 00:41:47.251
with the visual system,
with the auditory system.

00:41:47.251 --> 00:41:50.530
ADD, people talk about ADD a lot,

00:41:50.530 --> 00:41:53.640
is sort of baked into our
