01:05:21.650 --> 01:05:25.500
There is a phenomenon that appears real,

01:05:25.500 --> 01:05:28.460
that's called hallucinogen-persisting
perceptual disorder.

01:05:28.460 --> 01:05:29.623
It's in the DSM.

01:05:30.460 --> 01:05:32.153
A certain number of people,

01:05:32.153 --> 01:05:35.800
a very small number of
people percentage-wise

01:05:35.800 --> 01:05:37.140
who have used psychedelics,

01:05:37.140 --> 01:05:40.180
will have these persisting
perceptual disorders,

01:05:40.180 --> 01:05:41.790
like they'll see halos around things.

01:05:41.790 --> 01:05:43.083
They'll see some trails,

01:05:43.943 --> 01:05:47.463
like the after image is
following an object in motion.

01:05:49.530 --> 01:05:51.340
They'll see distortions in color.

01:05:51.340 --> 01:05:53.460
And it'll be like anything else

01:05:53.460 --> 01:05:55.700
that's a disorder in the DSM.

01:05:55.700 --> 01:05:57.230
It has to be clinically distressing,

01:05:57.230 --> 01:06:02.220
and it has to be persisting
over some number of months.

01:06:02.220 --> 01:06:04.950
And so very rare, very mysterious.

01:06:04.950 --> 01:06:06.893
Some of the keys to that are,

01:06:07.850 --> 01:06:09.900
amazingly, it's never been seen

01:06:09.900 --> 01:06:11.510
in the thousands of participants,

01:06:11.510 --> 01:06:12.740
either from the older era,

01:06:12.740 --> 01:06:15.327
from the late '50s to the early '70s,

01:06:15.327 --> 01:06:17.520
the people in psychedelic
studies with LSD,

01:06:17.520 --> 01:06:18.590
psilocybin, mescalin,

01:06:18.590 --> 01:06:20.200
and it's never been
seen in the Modern Era,

01:06:20.200 --> 01:06:22.750
again, now with thousands of participants

01:06:22.750 --> 01:06:26.560
at a number of centers like
ours throughout the world.

01:06:26.560 --> 01:06:30.550
