01:10:00.640 --> 01:10:03.760
But flashbacks can mean
a number of other things.

01:10:03.760 --> 01:10:06.480
I think the most common
thing people experiences is,

01:10:06.480 --> 01:10:08.603
what we call, state-dependent learning.

01:10:09.754 --> 01:10:12.280
It's returning yourself
to a similar context

01:10:12.280 --> 01:10:13.990
can bring back the same thoughts

01:10:13.990 --> 01:10:15.940
and emotions as the experience.

01:10:15.940 --> 01:10:18.800
So someone used mushrooms a week ago,

01:10:18.800 --> 01:10:22.563
now they do something like
they smoked some cannabis,

01:10:24.375 --> 01:10:26.443
or they take a warm bath,

01:10:27.450 --> 01:10:29.150
or they're simply relaxed,

01:10:29.150 --> 01:10:30.610
and it seems to come out of the blue,

01:10:30.610 --> 01:10:32.010
and all of a sudden, these,

01:10:32.010 --> 01:10:34.740
or they follow a thought
trail that takes them,

01:10:34.740 --> 01:10:35.810
that reminds them of their,

01:10:35.810 --> 01:10:39.960
and they find themselves in
that same experience again,

01:10:39.960 --> 01:10:42.060
I think that's more of
state-dependent learning.

01:10:42.060 --> 01:10:45.287
It's not the distressing
component that is in,

01:10:45.287 --> 01:10:47.480
and it's typically not perceptual.

01:10:47.480 --> 01:10:50.450
And then another class are just sort of

01:10:52.140 --> 01:10:54.570
