01:27:01.570 --> 01:27:03.423
The question is to me,

01:27:05.258 --> 01:27:07.180
what are the valuable exports, right?

01:27:07.180 --> 01:27:09.130
And where does the extreme lie?

01:27:09.130 --> 01:27:11.850
I mean, clearly, there's a problem

01:27:11.850 --> 01:27:16.850
with tinkering with reality
through pharmacology,

01:27:17.260 --> 01:27:19.210
and there's a benefit, it sounds like,

01:27:19.210 --> 01:27:21.460
to tinkering with reality

01:27:21.460 --> 01:27:23.110
through pharmacology.
- Yeah.

01:27:23.110 --> 01:27:25.710
- And what's so striking to me,

01:27:25.710 --> 01:27:29.350
is the elements of atypical experience,

01:27:29.350 --> 01:27:31.573
atypical representation of the self.

01:27:32.480 --> 01:27:37.330
So for the average person, right?

01:27:37.330 --> 01:27:38.930
Or for kids that are hearing this.

01:27:38.930 --> 01:27:40.690
Kids that are in their teens, right?

01:27:40.690 --> 01:27:41.720
- [Dr. Matthew] Yeah.

01:27:41.720 --> 01:27:44.858
- I want to talk about, what
are the dangers of psychedelics?

01:27:44.858 --> 01:27:46.620
It's something you don't
hear a lot about these days,

01:27:46.620 --> 01:27:48.980
and it's not because I'm
anti-psychedelic at all,

01:27:48.980 --> 01:27:51.433
but what are the dangers, right?

01:27:51.433 --> 01:27:55.513
If a kid or adult has a
predisposition toward, let's say,

01:27:58.360 --> 01:27:59.880
psychotic thinking, right?

01:27:59.880 --> 01:28:03.033
