01:47:51.156 --> 01:47:52.286
- Microdosing them?

01:47:52.286 --> 01:47:55.417
- Well, taking what would
be considered a microdose,

01:47:56.970 --> 01:48:00.813
and then doing some cognitive
measures before and after.

01:48:00.813 --> 01:48:01.863
And the types of things that,

01:48:01.863 --> 01:48:04.470
like a lot of cognitive
measures are measured on,

01:48:04.470 --> 01:48:07.510
the order of reaction
time in milliseconds.

01:48:07.510 --> 01:48:08.850
And the types of effects you get,

01:48:08.850 --> 01:48:09.890
as you could imagine,

01:48:09.890 --> 01:48:12.090
are ones that like would be,

01:48:12.090 --> 01:48:13.750
you would totally expect could be there

01:48:13.750 --> 01:48:15.610
from either a practice effect

01:48:15.610 --> 01:48:19.540
or an expectancy effect, a placebo effect.

01:48:19.540 --> 01:48:22.743
So for something like these claimed,

01:48:23.716 --> 01:48:26.330
you could imagine, a sort
of an increased focus,

01:48:26.330 --> 01:48:29.200
enhancement of cognition.

01:48:29.200 --> 01:48:32.060
These are going to be more subtle effects

01:48:32.060 --> 01:48:36.680
that you really need a
good placebo control for.

01:48:36.680 --> 01:48:40.710
The handful of studies that
have done that have shown,

01:48:40.710 --> 01:48:43.150
they've ranged from finding
no effect whatsoever

01:48:43.150 --> 01:48:44.950
to just a little bit of impairment,

01:48:44.950 --> 01:48:48.850
like impairing someone's
ability to do time estimation

01:48:48.850 --> 01:48:49.950
and production tasks.

01:48:49.950 --> 01:48:52.500
So you want an accurate sense of time,

01:48:52.500 --> 01:48:54.840
at least if you're
navigating in the real world.

01:48:54.840 --> 01:48:57.630
It's different if you're on
the couch on a heroic dose

01:48:57.630 --> 01:48:59.380
for therapeutic reasons where you're safe,

01:48:59.380 --> 01:49:02.291
but if you're crossing
the street, if you're...

01:49:02.291 --> 01:49:03.580
In your work life-
- You have to

01:49:03.580 --> 01:49:04.413
function in the world.

01:49:04.413 --> 01:49:05.246
- Yeah, which is the way people

01:49:05.246 --> 01:49:06.690
are claiming to use that.

01:49:06.690 --> 01:49:09.010
It helps them be a better CEO.

01:49:09.010 --> 01:49:10.570
You want an accurate sense of time.

01:49:10.570 --> 01:49:12.160
So if anything in the data suggests

01:49:12.160 --> 01:49:14.820
that it makes it a
little bit less accurate,

01:49:14.820 --> 01:49:17.480
and there's evidence that someone feels

01:49:18.460 --> 01:49:19.843
a little bit impaired,

01:49:20.707 --> 01:49:22.560
and they feel a little bit high.

01:49:22.560 --> 01:49:24.150
So in terms of...

01:49:24.150 --> 01:49:26.400
You call that abuse liability in research.

01:49:26.400 --> 01:49:28.900
Not surprising, you take
a little bit of a drug

01:49:28.900 --> 01:49:31.330
that can result in some type of a high,

01:49:31.330 --> 01:49:32.510
and you take a little, tiny bit of it,

01:49:32.510 --> 01:49:34.450
you'll feel a little bit high.

01:49:34.450 --> 01:49:37.670
So none of the...

01:49:37.670 --> 01:49:42.670
So far, no studies have shown
an increase in creativity,

01:49:44.290 --> 01:49:47.660
enhancement of any form of cognition,

01:49:47.660 --> 01:49:50.650
or a sustained improvement in mood.

01:49:50.650 --> 01:49:54.250
Now, no studies have actually looked at

01:49:56.258 --> 01:49:59.860
the system of microdosing that
the aficionados are claiming,

01:49:59.860 --> 01:50:02.390
and there's a couple of models out there.

01:50:02.390 --> 01:50:05.450
But folks like Paul Stamets, and others,

01:50:05.450 --> 01:50:06.930
they'll have particular formulas.

01:50:06.930 --> 01:50:09.050
They're like, you need to take it one day,

01:50:09.050 --> 01:50:10.530
and then take so many days off,

01:50:10.530 --> 01:50:11.800
and take it every four days.

01:50:11.800 --> 01:50:13.750
And I don't want to get
into whose model is what,

01:50:13.750 --> 01:50:15.000
but it's always something like that,

01:50:15.000 --> 01:50:18.610
some pattern of use,
usually not every day.

01:50:18.610 --> 01:50:21.590
And the claim is that, it's not just...

01:50:21.590 --> 01:50:23.250
You know, sometimes people get benefit

01:50:23.250 --> 01:50:25.080
that first time when they take it,

01:50:25.080 --> 01:50:27.940
but they really say, you
need to be on it for a while.

01:50:27.940 --> 01:50:28.990
Like a few weeks in,

01:50:28.990 --> 01:50:29.823
you may start to notice

01:50:29.823 --> 01:50:32.640
through this pattern of using it,

01:50:32.640 --> 01:50:35.470
and you're feeling the
benefits on those off days,

01:50:35.470 --> 01:50:40.470
like the three or two days
in between your active doses.

01:50:40.610 --> 01:50:41.610
So those are the claims.

01:50:41.610 --> 01:50:44.220
Again, we don't know that there's
any truth to that working,

01:50:44.220 --> 01:50:47.850
but studies have not
been done to model that.

01:50:47.850 --> 01:50:49.340
So that's a big caveat.

01:50:49.340 --> 01:50:50.360
We, as a field,

01:50:50.360 --> 01:50:53.030
I say, "we", as the scientific field,

01:50:53.030 --> 01:50:57.440
have not done the studies to really model

01:50:57.440 --> 01:50:59.520
what the real aficionados are claiming

01:51:00.860 --> 01:51:03.760
where the therapeutic benefits come from.

01:51:03.760 --> 01:51:06.520
That said, it's almost assuredly

01:51:06.520 --> 01:51:08.480
there's a good amount of placebo there.

01:51:08.480 --> 01:51:10.820
But the caveat to that is like,

01:51:10.820 --> 01:51:13.293
almost everything in
medicine or therapeutics,

01:51:14.568 --> 01:51:15.670
it's going to have some degree

01:51:15.670 --> 01:51:16.503
of placebo there.
- Sure.

01:51:16.503 --> 01:51:17.780
Belief effects are...

01:51:17.780 --> 01:51:20.710
I have a colleague at Stanford, Alia Crum,

01:51:20.710 --> 01:51:24.360
who has published really
beautiful work on belief effects,

01:51:24.360 --> 01:51:26.630
that show that, essentially,

01:51:26.630 --> 01:51:29.272
you give the same milkshake to two people,

01:51:29.272 --> 01:51:30.400
or two groups of people.

01:51:30.400 --> 01:51:32.217
You tell them that one
contains a lot of nutrients.

01:51:32.217 --> 01:51:34.810
The other is a low calorie shake.

01:51:34.810 --> 01:51:36.780
The insulin response
- Amazing.

01:51:36.780 --> 01:51:38.450
Yeah.
- varies dramatically

01:51:38.450 --> 01:51:39.283
between the two.

01:51:39.283 --> 01:51:40.880
Or two groups, rather,

01:51:40.880 --> 01:51:45.110
doing equivalent amounts
of physical movement,

01:51:45.110 --> 01:51:46.980
and you tell one group that
it's going to be good for them,

01:51:46.980 --> 01:51:47.890
and help them lose weight,

01:51:47.890 --> 01:51:50.130
and they lose, on average,
8 to 12 pounds more

01:51:50.130 --> 01:51:51.900
doing the exact same

01:51:51.900 --> 01:51:53.090
patterns of movement.
- Amazing.

01:51:53.090 --> 01:51:56.060
- And I think that these
belief effects boil down to

01:51:56.060 --> 01:51:58.600
all sorts of kind of
network-wide neuromodulation,

01:51:58.600 --> 01:51:59.670
things of that sort, but-
- And then the

01:51:59.670 --> 01:52:01.090
work at Harvard suggesting,

01:52:01.090 --> 01:52:03.200
that even if you don't have deception,

01:52:03.200 --> 01:52:04.410
you give a placebo, and say,

01:52:04.410 --> 01:52:06.834
this is a sugar pill,
- Right.

01:52:06.834 --> 01:52:08.010
- and tell them that,
- Right.

01:52:08.010 --> 01:52:09.230
- and they could still treat things.

01:52:09.230 --> 01:52:10.063
I think irritable bowel
- Right.

01:52:10.063 --> 01:52:11.780
- was the first thing they looked at.

01:52:11.780 --> 01:52:13.470
- Right.
- And so there's a huge...

01:52:13.470 --> 01:52:15.990
so there's a reality there.
- Right.

01:52:15.990 --> 01:52:17.560
- There's a necessity in developing drugs

01:52:17.560 --> 01:52:19.400
to make sure it's not only that.

01:52:19.400 --> 01:52:21.760
But in the actual practice of medicine,

01:52:21.760 --> 01:52:23.140
hopefully, what you're always getting

01:52:23.140 --> 01:52:25.180
is some underlying direct efficacy

01:52:25.180 --> 01:52:26.850
plus the placebo

01:52:26.850 --> 01:52:27.980
that enhances that.
- Right.

01:52:27.980 --> 01:52:30.530
- Now, it could be that this is...

01:52:30.530 --> 01:52:31.363
The real question is,

01:52:31.363 --> 01:52:32.530
is the microdosing,

01:52:32.530 --> 01:52:35.540
are those claims 100% placebo,

01:52:35.540 --> 01:52:37.620
or are they only part placebo,

01:52:37.620 --> 01:52:41.290
and part "real", quote/unquote, effect?

01:52:41.290 --> 01:52:45.140
My bet is, and this is
totally based on anecdotes,

01:52:45.140 --> 01:52:47.780
that I think there is probably a reality

01:52:47.780 --> 01:52:49.340
to the antidepressant effects.

01:52:49.340 --> 01:52:51.030
I find that more intriguing,

01:52:51.030 --> 01:52:51.863
- Well-
- because of the

01:52:51.863 --> 01:52:53.610
suffering with depression.
- Right.

01:52:53.610 --> 01:52:54.540
- Even if it's a...

01:52:54.540 --> 01:52:56.710
It wouldn't be as interesting as, I think,

01:52:56.710 --> 01:52:59.210
what we're doing with high dose psilocybin

01:52:59.210 --> 01:53:01.800
or psychedelics to treat depression.

01:53:01.800 --> 01:53:02.633
It would be...

01:53:02.633 --> 01:53:04.320
If this is developed,
and there's a reality,

01:53:04.320 --> 01:53:06.870
it would be more like a better,

01:53:06.870 --> 01:53:10.100
perhaps, a better SSRI, a better Prozac.

01:53:10.100 --> 01:53:10.933
- Which are similar.
- With that being said,

01:53:10.933 --> 01:53:13.950
we need more tools than
fewer tools in the toolbox.

01:53:13.950 --> 01:53:15.130
- Right.
- And it shouldn't be

01:53:15.130 --> 01:53:15.963
that surprise.

01:53:15.963 --> 01:53:17.110
Like even before,

01:53:17.110 --> 01:53:21.146
going back to the tricyclics,
and the MAO inhibitors,

01:53:21.146 --> 01:53:22.110
going back to the '50s,

01:53:22.110 --> 01:53:25.380
like augmenting extracellular serotonin

01:53:25.380 --> 01:53:26.993
in one way or another,

01:53:28.060 --> 01:53:28.990
for many people,

01:53:28.990 --> 01:53:31.350
leads to a reduction
in depressive symptoms.

01:53:31.350 --> 01:53:32.970
It wouldn't be that crazy

01:53:32.970 --> 01:53:37.010
for chronically stimulating a
subtype of serotonin receptor

01:53:37.010 --> 01:53:38.880
that you have an antidepressant effect.

01:53:38.880 --> 01:53:41.760
So I think, if I had to put my bets on it,

01:53:41.760 --> 01:53:42.930
if there's anything real,

01:53:42.930 --> 01:53:44.470
it is in that category.

01:53:44.470 --> 01:53:45.590
Although, I'm very open to like,

01:53:45.590 --> 01:53:48.180
maybe there is something
to the creativity,

01:53:48.180 --> 01:53:51.010
to the improved cognition,

01:53:51.010 --> 01:53:53.900
which covers many
domains in and of itself.

01:53:53.900 --> 01:53:58.900
But my greatest hopes are on
the antidepressant effects.

01:54:00.550 --> 01:54:02.150
That said, in the big picture,

01:54:02.150 --> 01:54:04.940
I think the most interesting
thing about psychedelics

01:54:04.940 --> 01:54:06.600
are the heroic doses.

01:54:06.600 --> 01:54:07.433
I mean, the idea that you can

01:54:07.433 --> 01:54:09.550
give something one, two, three times,

01:54:09.550 --> 01:54:12.287
and you see improvements
in depression months later,

01:54:12.287 --> 01:54:13.970
- Right.
- and in addiction

01:54:15.020 --> 01:54:16.320
over a year later,

01:54:16.320 --> 01:54:18.530
and with these, people dealing with

01:54:18.530 --> 01:54:20.110
potentially terminal illness,

01:54:20.110 --> 01:54:23.433
I mean, I'm interested in big effects.

01:54:23.433 --> 01:54:24.266
- [Dr. Huberman] Right.

01:54:24.266 --> 01:54:25.160
- And I don't think
you're ever going to get

01:54:25.160 --> 01:54:26.630
the really big effects.

01:54:26.630 --> 01:54:28.680
There's also some concern

01:54:28.680 --> 01:54:31.460
that almost all of these common psych,

01:54:31.460 --> 01:54:34.060
the more common psychedelics,
even counting MDMA,

01:54:34.060 --> 01:54:37.320
they have serotonin to be agonist effects,

01:54:37.320 --> 01:54:39.620
and agonizing serotonin 2B

01:54:41.320 --> 01:54:46.147
has been shown to lead to
heart valve formation problems,

01:54:47.400 --> 01:54:50.810
morphology issues, so valvulopathy.

01:54:50.810 --> 01:54:53.510
And so this is why fen-phen
was pulled from the market.

01:54:53.510 --> 01:54:54.940
- The diet drug?
- Yes.

01:54:54.940 --> 01:54:57.100
- A very effective diet drug.
- Right, right.

01:54:57.100 --> 01:54:59.770
And it was the portion of that combination

01:54:59.770 --> 01:55:04.770
that had the serotonin 2B
activity that was the problem.

01:55:05.040 --> 01:55:07.240
And so we don't know...

01:55:07.240 --> 01:55:09.480
So all of the toxicologists

01:55:09.480 --> 01:55:12.050
I've ever spoken to about this would say,

01:55:12.050 --> 01:55:13.300
and cardiologists say, like,

01:55:13.300 --> 01:55:16.400
look, hey, if there
was some concern there,

01:55:16.400 --> 01:55:18.390
it's not applicable to the whole idea

01:55:18.390 --> 01:55:19.890
of you taking something a few times

01:55:19.890 --> 01:55:21.940
therapeutically within a lifetime.

01:55:21.940 --> 01:55:26.200
But the idea of taking something

01:55:26.200 --> 01:55:29.000
twice a week for years...

01:55:29.000 --> 01:55:31.260
I mean, even the hippies back in the '60s

01:55:31.260 --> 01:55:32.610
weren't doing that, right?

01:55:32.610 --> 01:55:34.232
There's not even these...

01:55:34.232 --> 01:55:39.232
And even if there was some
heart valve disease problem

01:55:39.910 --> 01:55:42.710
that stemmed from psychedelic use,

01:55:42.710 --> 01:55:44.360
who's connecting those dots?

01:55:44.360 --> 01:55:46.340
That's not showing up
in the clinical charts

01:55:46.340 --> 01:55:47.590
for anyone to figure out.

01:55:48.670 --> 01:55:49.790
And just theoretically,

01:55:49.790 --> 01:55:52.320
there is more of a concern,

01:55:52.320 --> 01:55:55.270
if something's going to
happen with heart valves,

01:55:55.270 --> 01:55:58.940
it's more likely that
that issues would arise

01:55:58.940 --> 01:56:00.190
when someone's taking these things,

01:56:00.190 --> 01:56:04.250
like, yeah, say, twice a
week for the next five years.

01:56:04.250 --> 01:56:05.590
And so I do want to throw that out

01:56:05.590 --> 01:56:07.060
to people to really consider.

01:56:07.060 --> 01:56:07.950
- Right, yeah.

01:56:07.950 --> 01:56:08.783
It's something I hadn't heard before.

01:56:08.783 --> 01:56:12.040
That in micro sounds safer, microdosing,

01:56:12.040 --> 01:56:14.280
as opposed to heroic or macrodosing,

01:56:14.280 --> 01:56:16.430
and yet, unless...

01:56:16.430 --> 01:56:18.380
And in the context of your lab,

01:56:18.380 --> 01:56:21.000
and other labs doing similar work,

01:56:21.000 --> 01:56:22.050
you've got this,

01:56:22.050 --> 01:56:23.390
people checking blood pressure.

01:56:23.390 --> 01:56:25.100
You've got people that
are really monitoring

01:56:25.100 --> 01:56:27.320
your psychological and physical safety.

01:56:27.320 --> 01:56:28.870
When people are out there microdosing,

01:56:28.870 --> 01:56:30.930
it sounds like there's the potential,

01:56:30.930 --> 01:56:35.450
either through this
serotonin 5H2B receptor,

01:56:35.450 --> 01:56:36.450
or other mechanism,

01:56:36.450 --> 01:56:38.140
that maybe there could be some common

01:56:38.140 --> 01:56:40.113
cumulative negative effects,

01:56:41.560 --> 01:56:44.390
and I think that's a really
important consideration.

01:56:44.390 --> 01:56:46.010
So I'm glad you brought it up.

01:56:46.010 --> 01:56:47.600
What about kids?

01:56:47.600 --> 01:56:50.740
So the brain is very
plastic early in life.

01:56:50.740 --> 01:56:53.340
It becomes less plastic as we age.

01:56:53.340 --> 01:56:54.173
- Yeah.
- Although,

01:56:54.173 --> 01:56:56.170
it maintains some degree of plasticity

01:56:56.170 --> 01:56:57.690
throughout the lifespan.

01:56:57.690 --> 01:56:59.470
The year 25,

01:56:59.470 --> 01:57:01.680
not the year 25,

01:57:01.680 --> 01:57:04.450
but rather, the age 25 years,

01:57:04.450 --> 01:57:06.930
is sort of an inflection point

01:57:06.930 --> 01:57:10.440
where the rigidity of the nervous system

01:57:10.440 --> 01:57:11.660
seems to really take off.

01:57:11.660 --> 01:57:12.980
Of course, people don't wake up

01:57:12.980 --> 01:57:14.130
on their 25th birthday,

01:57:14.130 --> 01:57:16.340
and find they have no neural plasticity,

01:57:16.340 --> 01:57:18.450
whereas the day before, they had a lot.

01:57:18.450 --> 01:57:19.970
It's plus or minus,

01:57:19.970 --> 01:57:20.803
- Yeah.
- whatever it is,

01:57:20.803 --> 01:57:21.670
a year or two,

01:57:21.670 --> 01:57:23.743
but depends on the individual.

01:57:25.560 --> 01:57:30.560
However, the young brain is very plastic,

01:57:30.700 --> 01:57:35.700
and I could imagine, there
could be great risks,

01:57:36.040 --> 01:57:37.470
who knows, maybe even benefits,

01:57:37.470 --> 01:57:40.070
but I'm certainly not
thinking about those.

01:57:40.070 --> 01:57:42.660
I'm mainly thinking about the risks

01:57:42.660 --> 01:57:46.260
for young people taking psychedelics.

01:57:46.260 --> 01:57:49.120
Are there any trials looking at people...

01:57:49.120 --> 01:57:49.990
In clinical trials,

01:57:49.990 --> 01:57:51.340
this would be under the age of 18,

01:57:51.340 --> 01:57:54.490
Has anyone explored
this in a rigorous way,

01:57:54.490 --> 01:57:57.790
given the potential to
exacerbate psychotic symptoms

01:57:57.790 --> 01:57:59.590
and bipolar symptoms in some people?

01:58:01.030 --> 01:58:03.350
Is there a heightened risk of that?

01:58:03.350 --> 01:58:05.530
What's the story with age of use

01:58:05.530 --> 01:58:07.620
and psychedelics for therapeutic purposes?

01:58:07.620 --> 01:58:10.110
- There's no formal research.

01:58:10.110 --> 01:58:13.120
Although, there's a very high
chance that there will be.

01:58:13.120 --> 01:58:14.870
And so this is one of the
very interesting things

01:58:14.870 --> 01:58:16.740
folks may not realize

01:58:16.740 --> 01:58:19.640
or appreciate about the
FDA approval process.

01:58:19.640 --> 01:58:22.160
So the FDA already, in multiple instances,

01:58:22.160 --> 01:58:25.940
has signaled that they
want to see those studies.

01:58:25.940 --> 01:58:26.890
- Before?

01:58:26.890 --> 01:58:28.700
- Well, not before it's approved

01:58:28.700 --> 01:58:32.820
as necessarily as for adults,

01:58:32.820 --> 01:58:34.380
but they're going to
eventually want to see...

01:58:34.380 --> 01:58:38.310
In fact, so the MAPS group
that's developing MDMA for PTSD,

01:58:38.310 --> 01:58:42.160
they've already signaled
that that's kind of

01:58:42.160 --> 01:58:44.940
on the list of interest.

01:58:44.940 --> 01:58:49.140
And there's even some
incentives in the FDA pathways

01:58:51.200 --> 01:58:55.880
for incentivizing folks to
explore that use in young people.

01:58:55.880 --> 01:58:57.880
I know in some of the
work that I helped with

01:58:57.880 --> 01:59:02.880
in pushing psilocybin into
phase 2B clinical research,

01:59:05.100 --> 01:59:09.620
the FDA said, "Well why
can't you give this to kids?"

01:59:09.620 --> 01:59:12.870
It's like, are you aware that depression

01:59:12.870 --> 01:59:15.423
is a problem with adolescents?

